title.narrative: Government authorities at national and subnational level have enhanced governance and partnership capacities to manage a multi- sectoral nutrition response

description.narrative: Strengthened evidence-based advocacy for advancing nutrition contributed to increased districts' average spending for multisectoral nutrition interventions from TZS 47 million in 2017/18 to TZS 70 million in 2018/19, and increased proportion of regions spending at least 50% of the planned domestic budget, from 4% in 2017/18 to 27% in 2018/19. The National Nutrition Compact was also signed at Ward and Village level in UNICEF focus regions, which is likely to increase community commitments and social accountability for nutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2020
